title: Three city golfers compete at state
text:
October 20, 2015 
Advertisement 
Andover Â— Free State High junior Anne Goebel shot a 113 and took 68th place to lead all city golfers at the Class 6A state girls golf tournament on Monday at Terradyne Country Club. 
It was the best finish for Goebel, who has qualfied for state in all three years of her high school career. Free State sophomore Tori Hoopingarner finished in 89th, firing a 127. Lawrence High freshman Beatrice Lopez was 91st with a 135.
